Blood Sugar & Pressure Tracker
Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 26 October 2024
Thank you for choosing to use the Blood Sugar & Pressure Tracker (referred to as "the App"). At Blood Sugar & Blood Pressure Tracker, we prioritize your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy provides a comprehensive overview of how we collect, use, share, and protect your information when you use our services. By accessing or using our App, you consent to the practices outlined in this policy.
1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Data
In order to provide you with a personalized experience and improve our services, we may ask you to provide certain personally identifiable information. This information may include, but is not limited to:
Health Data
: You may choose to input health-related information, such as:
Weight
Height
Menstrual cycle details
Any other health metrics you wish to track
Note:
Any personal information you provide is stored solely on your device and is not transmitted to us directly. You will be notified of any data collection when first using the app.
1.2 Usage Data
In addition to personal data, we automatically collect information about your interaction with our Service. This data helps us understand how our app is used and allows us to improve its functionality. Usage Data may include:
Device Information
: This includes details about your device, such as:
Internet Protocol (IP) address
Device model and brand
Operating system and version
Log Data
: Information related to your usage of the app, including:
Pages and features you visit within the app
Date and time of visits
Duration of time spent on specific pages or features
Other Diagnostic Data
: Unique identifiers assigned to your device may help us diagnose issues and enhance the user experience.
2. How We Use Your Information
The information we collect serves several purposes, including:
Service Provision
: To provide you with the features and functionalities of our App for a seamless experience.
Personalization
: To customize your experience based on your preferences and usage patterns.
Health Monitoring
: To assist you in tracking your blood pressure and blood sugar levels effectively, offering reminders for scheduled readings.
Feedback and Improvement
: To analyze usage data for improving our services and developing new features.
Communication
: To send you updates, notifications, and information related to the App, including changes to our policies.
3. Permissions Required
Our App requires specific permissions to function optimally and deliver a seamless experience. These permissions include:
ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE:
Accesses network information to check the availability and type of network connection.
INTERNET:
Provides internet connectivity for real-time data updates and app analytics.
SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM:
Allows the app to set precise alarms, triggering at exact times even in low-power modes to ensure timely health reminders.
USE_EXACT_ALARM:
Enables setting precise alarm notifications for accurate health tracking alerts.
WAKE_LOCK:
Keeps the device’s CPU active when the screen is off to ensure notifications and alarms are delivered accurately.
QUICKBOOT_POWERON:
Ensures reinitialization of alarms or reminders after device reboots to maintain scheduled health monitoring.
SET_ALARM:
Lets users set alarms within the device’s clock or alarm app, helpful for regular monitoring.
RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED:
Re-establishes app functionality after the system reboots, preserving scheduled reminders and health tracking.
POST_NOTIFICATIONS:
Posts notifications, sending timely reminders for scheduled health activities and updates.
CAMERA:
Accesses the device’s camera for capturing photos or videos if needed within the app.
FLASHLIGHT:
Enables control of the flashlight, potentially useful for enhancing notifications.
VIBRATE:
Allows the app to trigger device vibration for reminders or alarm notifications, reinforcing their alerting purpose.
These permissions support the app's goal of consistent and reliable health monitoring. If you need any modifications or more details, feel free to ask.
4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
Your personal information is shared only in the following circumstances:
Third-Party Service Providers
: We may employ trusted third-party companies and individuals to facilitate our Service ("Service Providers"), process data on our behalf, or provide services related to the App. These third parties are obligated to maintain the confidentiality of your information and are prohibited from using it for any other purpose.
Legal Obligations
: We may disclose your personal information if required to do so by law, or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or a government agency), to protect and defend our rights or property, or to prevent potential wrongdoing in connection with the Service.
5. Security of Your Personal Data
We take the security of your personal information seriously and employ industry-standard security measures to protect it, including:
Data Encryption
: We use encryption to safeguard your data both in transit and at rest.
Access Controls
: Strict access controls limit access to your personal information only to authorized personnel.
Regular Security Assessments
: We conduct regular security assessments and updates to our systems to identify vulnerabilities and enhance our security posture.
While we strive to protect your personal information, please be aware that no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
6. Data Retention
Data stored on your device is deleted upon app uninstallation. We do not retain any of your health data on external servers, as it is solely stored on your device.
7. Your Rights
As a user of Blood Sugar & Blood Pressure Tracker, you have the following rights concerning your personal information:
Access
: You have the right to request copies of your personal information.
Correction
: You have the right to request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete information.
Deletion
: You can request the deletion of your personal data, subject to any legal obligations we may have to retain it.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at the email provided below.
Contact Email
:
tannerbrookstanner@gmail.com
8. Children’s Privacy
Our services are not directed at individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 16. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 16, we will take immediate steps to delete such information. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.
9. Links to Other Websites
Our App may contain links to external websites that are not operated by us. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to that third party's site. We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit. We have no control over, and assume no responsibility for, the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party sites or services.
10. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the effective date at the top of this policy. You will also be notified within the app. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates or changes.
11. Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our practices, please feel free to contact us at:
tannerbrookstanner@gmail.com
